Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has called Buba Galadima, a spokesperson for the Atiku Campaign Organisation, as its first witness in the ongoing presidential election tribunal sitting in Abuja. Galadima is a former ally of President Muhammadu Buhari, whose victory in the February 23rd presidential election is being contested by Atiku Abubakar and his party, PDP. When Galadima was asked why he fell out with the President, he said Buhari has failed to deliver on the promise of giving Nigerians good and quality leadership. Being a fighter of justice and equality, he added that he has nothing personal against Buhari other than bad leadership. More to follow…  